                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102H/326: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-21T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1919—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received June 21—11:04 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I beg to request immediate instructions my telegram of June 9, 9 a.m. [<hi
                        rend="italic">p.m.</hi>] Russian Minister willing to accept statement that
                    where any American objects to application [of] any administrative act [of]
                    municipal authorities, matter will be referred to American consul. American
                    interests consider highly important to accept without delay.</p>
                <closer>[No signature indicated]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
